  conceptualFramework: "MDD is best understood as a network excitability and connectivity disorder characterised by three core circuit-level abnormalities: (1) DMN hyperactivity driving rumination and negative self-reference; (2) CEN hypoactivity impairing cognitive control and emotion regulation; and (3) Limbic-SN dysregulation perpetuating threat bias and blunted reward processing. The FNON framework targets these abnormalities simultaneously using multi-modal neuromodulation, with the S-O-Z-O sequence designed to stabilise autonomic arousal, upregulate prefrontal control, engage deep limbic circuits, and consolidate network changes through activity-dependent behavioural practice.",

