  polarityPrincipleText: "In MDD according to the SOZO FNON concept: Anode is applied over the left DLPFC (F3) to increase hypoactive prefrontal excitability — this is the most replicated and evidence-based montage across all MDD subtypes. Cathode over right DLPFC (F4) for classical unilateral configuration, or over Pz for DMN suppression effects, or extracephalic to minimise inhibition of the therapeutic network. Bilateral DLPFC anodal stimulation (HDCkit dual-channel F3+F4) is used for treatment-resistant and cognitive phenotypes requiring maximum bilateral prefrontal engagement. Right DLPFC anodal (F4) is preferred for insomnia-predominant and hyperarousal presentations where right-hemisphere prefrontal modulation reduces nocturnal arousal.",
