  medicationSectionTitle: "tDCS Application During Ongoing SSRI/SNRI Treatment",
  medicationNibsText: "The majority of MDD patients receiving FNON neuromodulation will be on concurrent SSRI or SNRI pharmacotherapy (sertraline, escitalopram, venlafaxine). Serotonergic and noradrenergic agents can modulate cortical excitability and may enhance tDCS-induced neuroplasticity through shared intracellular signalling pathways involving BDNF upregulation and cAMP-CREB cascades. The treating Doctor should document all psychotropic medications, review for CYP450 interactions if TPS is combined with tricyclic antidepressants or MAOIs (which are contraindicated with MAOIs), and consider timing NIBS sessions to coincide with pharmacological effect peaks. Sertraline and escitalopram at therapeutic doses appear to have neutral-to-positive interactions with anodal L-DLPFC tDCS based on available pilot data. Sedating antidepressants (mirtazapine, amitriptyline) should be considered when scheduling session timing due to their potential to reduce cortical excitability and limit tDCS-induced plasticity. Lithium augmentation does not contraindicate tDCS but requires careful monitoring given its narrow therapeutic index.",

